General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Community Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

Why should I play this class?

Sharpshooter is a very relaxed class and is relatively simple, it has two main builds that function similar to Sorceress and other classes, where you have Death Strike which is a burst build and Loyal Companion which is a consistent DPS build. Sharpshooter is a non-directional class meaning where you are relative to the boss does not matter, making it relatively easier to play compared to other classes.

How does my identity work?

Sharpshooter generates meter with specific skills with tripods that boost the meter generation. When your hawk is summoned it is slowly draining and can only be maintained with consistent use of meter generation.

This hawk auto attacks dealing damage and applying a small amount of stagger.

Wings of Storm (Z)

This makes the hawk do an AoE attack onto the selected area.

Last Rush (X)

This makes the hawk dive into the target location, dealing a decent amount of damage but “suiciding” the hawk. Turning off your meter.

How do I decide on a build?

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

Here’s a short summary of the builds. For further information, read their respective sections of this document.

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight while Burst synergies are much more infrequent.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

Death Strike

Written by Soggy Lumps and Heated

Playstyle

Generate meter, summon hawk and suicide it into the boss giving yourself a big DPS increase, continuously regenerate meter within your rotation to keep high uptime on your DPS buff.

Stat Allocation

Aim for 100% Crit Rate, this includes tripods, synergies, and any other source of Crit you can gain. After that you generally want to dump the rest into Swift. Swift is not a significant DPS gain but is decent QOL for helping your rotation be fluid. Spec is mostly useless as it only gives you a minor damage gain, but on a bracelet it can be fine if you are gaining other damage lines and Crit.

Sharpshooter Stat Calculator

You can swap a ring to Swift/Spec if you have 100% Crit, however the gain here is very minimal and this is a very min-max situation and based on your party.

Hallucination Level 3 + Adrenaline 1 + 1594 Crit = 90% Crit Rate

Hallucination Level 3 + Adrenaline 1 + 1840 Crit = 99% Crit Rate

Awakening

Goldeneye

Spin in a giant gust of wind doing notable damage and go invisible.

This is generally for fast casting and decent AoE for things like Chaos Dungeons. Higher damage if you have an easy to swap to Fenrir preset to start the fight. Create an awakening swap and use Fenrir at the beginning to cheese meter.

Should be used for highest damage potential. Requires Awakening Swap to see that potential.

Fenrir

Charge up a Giant Wolf that sucks and does mediocre damage, but overcharging the skill grants Full Hawk Meter.

Can be used to cheese a full hawk at the beginning of the fight and is a semi-decent awakening option. It can also be used as a backup meter gen option should you miss your Silver Master skills.

Should be used for Quality of Life.

FAQ: Death Strike

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Can I run Spec?

Meter generation is now so significant that just wealth runes and decent tripod level are solid generation without any spec increase. However there are Spec variants of the build that can be played, however there is no significant reason to play them other than novelty.

Should I use Fenrir/Goldeneye?

Probably Goldeneye if you want to be at your peak performance, the only reason Fenrir is recommended is because newer players likely won’t do well with Awakening swaps or the average person just not wanting to put in the effort to edge the extra damage. You can push an extra 1-2% damage with a well timed Goldeneye as opposed to Fenrir which many will miss ticks on. If you are wondering what an Awakening swap is, essentially you make a preset with Awakening 3, Dominion gear set, and high Swiftness and Fenrir equipped, use Fenrir for full meter, then swap back to your standard build (this should be a bit over a minute CD on your awakening), you could also whale on stimulants.

Why not Nightmare?

9/7 Builds overcap crit which can make it do good damage but only if you are not hitting boundless. If you use Unlimited Mana in Trixion the set looks really good but in real scenarios you will be consistently proccing boundless making it objectively worse. There is a Crit/Spec build that is viable but most people just brainlessly copy Loawa rankings on whoever is the “top rank” without thinking or doing math hence why you see many Koreans run it, additionally many have quit the game or are taking break and are still using Nightmare from before.

Why Adrenaline 3 in 5x3 and not 5x3+1?

Early game you only have 5x3, level 2 set and probably lower quality accessories with a relic bracelet. Later on you can gain a free +1 engraving, higher quality on your accessories and your set upgrades. Adrenaline 3 gives us more overall damage when we are lacking those early crit sources, but once we gain 3% more crit from Hallucination level 3 and higher quality with the drop of Adrenaline 3 to 1 we end up with similar max crit rate while being able to invest in other damage engravings for a higher damage output.

Loyal Companion

Written by Soggy Lumps and Civo

Playstyle

Is a simple non-directional playstyle that has a large amount of versatility in building with builds that can be longer cooldown with higher numbers or significantly more movement speed and attack speed with lower cooldowns and even being able to utilize the Dominion set. This class engraving allows you to tailor your build to your playstyle, utilizing Summon Silverhawk and keeping 100% uptime your hawk consistently deals damages Wings of Storm (Z)  and the hawk buffs you and gives your teammates movement speed. Fenrir’s Messenger is utilized to instantly generate meter and upkeep 100% hawk uptime.

Stat Allocation

Your goal is to aim for a near 100% crit chance. This can include synergies or not depending on your personal choices. After that dump the rest into Swiftness or Specialization. Utilize the calculator to find out how much Crit you need; this is impacted by Stats, Relic Set, Engravings, Card Sets, and Synergies.

After getting your Crit you can decide on dumping your leftover stats into Spec or Swift, Spec results in the highest damage multiplier while Swift allows you to cap Attack and Movement speed and having a lower cooldown rotation.

Sharpshooter Stat Calculator

Can help you properly allocate stats for sharpshooter builds.

The following is based on Trixion testing with high quality accessories with the standard builds shown later in the document (evasive was not used) and standard 5x3 engravings.

Using the 50-50 Crit/Spec build as the baseline

  • Full Spec is about 5% weaker
  • Crit/Swift is about 7% weaker
  • At 5x3+1 and level 3 sets, Crit/Swift ties with/slightly edges out Full Spec
  • Full Swift is about 10% weaker
  • Dominion build is noticeably stronger (over 10%) but unlike the other builds it is a relatively inaccurate representation of the damage you will be doing in an actual fight, due to such low cooldowns that any movement is a dps loss

Gear Set

Salvation is used in both the suggested 50-50 builds since crit is attained through stats and salvation gives the best damage increase, due to nightmare not affecting bird damage. Since our damage scales better with crit vs swift/spec, and Salv is overall a better set than Hallu, this is a straight damage upgrade vs running lower crit stat with Hallu set.

Hallucination  is used in full swift or spec builds to supplement the low crit rate. Generally not suggested but it is viable.

4 Dominion + 2 Nightmare  is used alternatively for a spammier playstyle and is viable however it requires awakening management to utilize the set. Nightmare is required to help upkeep mana costs and Adrenaline is required to offset the lost Crit. This is not recommended for newer players.

 Nightmare is not recommended due to the DPS loss in exchange for mana comfort. This is because Nightmare buffs damage spells that cost mana and your hawk has no mana involved so your Relic Set is not impacting 10-25% of your damage. To solve your mana problems, address your runes, tripods, and food, read the FAQ section for more info on mana. It is better to just play the Dominion build.

and why you would choose specific combinations of Engravings to make a build.

Mandatory

Loyal Companion

Move Speed 4+4%

Hawk Aoe Radius +60%

Duration +30/60/100%

Mark Enemy +3/7/12%

Attack Power +1/3/6%

  • Best Damage increasing engraving.

Keen Blunt Weapon

+10/25/50% Crit Damage

10% Chance of

-20% Damage

  • Due to Tripods already giving 40% Crit by default this engraving is a MUST it outperforms other engravings.

Non-Directional Attacks

  • This is very good engraving on Sharpshooter, this is because nearly all of your damage is non-directional.

Cursed Doll

+3/8/16% Attack Power

-25% Healing

  • Is a great option for a damage engraving since it is non conditional and the only downside is the negative effect.

Raid Captain

+4/8.8/18% Damage

at max Move Speed (140%)

  • With your Synergy + Support and adding in some swiftness you can easily reach the cap for MS.
  • It beats other engravings at 16%+

and Move Speed

READ FIRST

          

Loyal Companion needs to upkeep their hawk with Silver Master enabled on a skill, which skill you do this on doesn’t matter too much but will change how you upkeep slightly. Hawk Shot makes it effortless to maintain while taking it on other skills can give you space to improve Hawk Shot’s mana or attack speed. You can even run multiple if you really want to. Additionally you can slot in Wealth runes if you want.

FAQ: Loyal Companion

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

What’s the best build?

In reality the damage difference between builds and skill selections is not significant enough to warrant degrading your experience over. 50-50 Crit Spec has the highest theoretical potential out of the meta builds (Dominion has higher but unlikely to actually perform better in a real fight) but in a real raid and depending on skill this can really change. I recommend either of the 50/50 builds (crit/swift or crit/spec) due to them having fairly similar performance late game as well as both beating out their full spec/full swift counterparts. Ultimately which you should choose comes down to personal preference and I suggest messing around in Trixion if you are struggling to decide.

I want to run Crit-Swift but can’t reach 50% Crit and 40% MS?

A 50/50 Crit/Swift build at end game with 5x3 will generally end up at around 45% Crit Rate and 37% move speed (accounting for lvl 2 yearning). This neither hits the 50% crit rate goal that Loyal builds generally have, nor does it meet the 40% move speed goal that Raid Captain users generally want to hit. Even taking this into account, this build still outperforms the full swiftness build. It also means this build will scale well into the future, as when you get level 3 sets and +1 adrenaline you will be at 50% Crit and 39% move speed (this is what causes Crit/Swift to go from 7% damage behind Crit/Spec to about 4-5% damage behind). So while the numbers look awkward, it’s still a perfectly viable set up in the current state of the game, although it is a bit demanding on quality of accessories. If you’re not able to get high quality accessories, you can also consider going the route of building 50% crit and then dumping the rest into swift and running Mass Increase or Cursed Doll instead of Raid Captain. At 5x3 this does 1% or so less damage than 50/50 crit/swift but the gap grows wider when 50/50 gets closer to reaching those 50% crit and 40% move speed benchmarks.

Is evasive shot worth a Dmg Gem and running at 12?

In theory kinda yes but in practice kinda no. This is because Evasive Shot when used perfectly is only an absolute maximum of a 2-3% DPS increase. This requires you to use it on cooldown, head attack it every time, and completely drop your counter and ability to level another skill for utility. Not to mention the mana drain. It is a pretty overhyped skill in this regard because for the majority of players the damage gain would be barely 1%. Even if you do decide to use Evasive as a damage ability, Charged Shot & Silverhawk cooldown gems are better choices for the last gem slot, so an evasive gem should never be used.

Should I use Conviction + Judgment?

You can, if you are sacrificing your focus runes for them, you may have some mana problems due to it not giving back nearly as much mana as focus runes save you. It is a viable rune choice, but make sure you are using legendary. Common abilities used are multihits, things like Sharpshooter, Arrow Shower, Bladestorm, etc. The standard placements are Conviction on Sharpshooter and Judgment on Arrow Shower in which you reactively cast the latter when you see the former proc, or Conviction on Arrow Shower and Judgment on Sharpshooter, where you deliberately hold Sharpshooter and cast it right after you see Conviction trigger. The former does not impact your DPS as much, but the latter triggers faster and has a lower probability of failing to trigger.

I’m having mana problems. What should I do?

Always have a support, and use the mana tripods if necessary, make sure you are always using Focus runes and get food as a last resort, you can craft them for free at your stronghold.

Why not go Full Swift or Full Spec?

They are simply inferior builds due to Sharpshooter’s high value for Crit.

Full Swift used to be better but due to these changes it is just inferior.

  1. Severe Mana Issues
  2. Awakening No Longer required for Meter
  3. Hawk Shot new skill no Crit tripods (12% of ur damage)
  4. Charged Shot now uses Fast Fire tripod losing crit (12% of ur damage)

For Full Spec it is much simpler, in simple your Spec scaling is not as good as Crit so nearly any situation where you can gain Crit vs Spec, Crit will win.

This is why we use Cursed Doll over Adrenaline because…

Cursed Doll + Crit Stat > Adrenaline + Spec Stat
